This is the first epicurious recipe I'll ever review even though I've been using the site for a while. Its just everything a winter soup should be... comforting and thick, it heats up your insides. It is elegant enough that my family has requested it for the past two Christmases for guests, but easy enough to make that we'll reheat it for week night dinners until the whole big bowl is gone. Quite important though is that I only made it with acorn squash once. Have you ever tried to peel an acorn squash? Forget it! Using whole fresh butternut squash makes a huge difference. Yes, this does require time and a work out, but I've made it twice with pre-cut squash and it just plain wasn't as good. The same goes for the spices... spring for the fresh ones. Also, the gruyere croutons are nice, but not necessary. Serve it with a hunk of a white boule and everyone will be happy! PS. Having a hand blender really helps.

