I'll try to be kind, but I must admit I am utterly baffled at the mostly positive 375 reviews of this recipe. I truly don't get it. I find this recipe to be bland, dull, and certainly not worthy of dinner guests. I followed the recipe as written with one exception -- I roasted the squash instead of boiling. It has no depth of flavor. The Gruyere and the croutons make for some interest, but only as a means of finishing the bowl of soup. Somewhere I have packed away Gunter Seeger's recipe for a similar soup. As I recall it had a baked apple placed in the soup plate. The Epicurious recipe needs something--a reduction of apple cider, white wine, maybe, a little nutmeg. It needs something to deepen the flavor. Sorry, I really wanted to like this soup, but that didn't happen.

