For quite some time I have been making a roasted butternut squash soup that was a hybrid of different recipes. I thought it was pretty good, but my bubble was burst when my husband recently told me it was merely okay. So tonight I decided to try a different recipe, and gave this one a shot. It actually was a vast improvement over my other soup, which I thought was pretty good to begin with. I made a few changes, though. I used only butternut squash, used fat free half and half instead of whipping cream and did not use fresh thyme since I didn't have any on hand. I also didn't make the gruyere croutons but instead topped the soup with walnuts and blue cheese. It really was delicious. I should add that I normally roast the squash when I make butternut squash soup but didn't this time. While it was hard to peel and cube the squash, I find it equally hard to slice the whole squash in half for roasting. Plus you have an extra dish to clean, so I don't really think it is all that much extra work just to peel and cube it.

Rating: 4
