I made a few subs/changes but the guidelines here create a beautiful winter soup with lots of room for improv! There was a vegetarian in our midst so I used water instead of broth, adding more throughout for consistency (prob ~4-5 cups). I used butternut squash only, omitted thyme and sage, added about 1/2 tsp. nutmeg and salt & pepper to taste & a healthy amount of parmigiano reggiano; I used a little less than 2tsps. brown sugar for the sugar. It turned out more savory than sweet, a little spicy from the pepper and my four guests raved! One of the omnivores even asked if there was chicken stock in it. I'll definitely use the base and proportions again for more hearty winter soups.

