Rating: 4
OK. Start with a heavy dutch oven. Then rinse the squash, and section it. Depending on the squash either 4ths or more... Halve the butter that you cook the onion and garlic in... Then you spoon seeds and pulp and add that to the onions and garlic at the tail end of their being cooked. You then proceed to cook for about 5 more minutes - add broth and steam squash (market bought $3.00 stailess steamer) pieces over seeds, onions, garlic and 1.5 cups of water. Do this for 25 minutes. Remove squash and cool. Sieve seeds, onions ets. Chop 1/4 large onion to same consitency as directed and add to dutch oven with remaining butter. Cook for 10 minutes, add required broth (vegetable worked very well) scoop out cooled squash discard skins and add liquid from first step. Add herbs a touch of sugar and cream (less than called for) and puree with hand blender. Amazing - laughably so... I'm telling you - the steaming of the squash over the salvaged seeds and pulp really round out the soup. You barely need any IF any sugar or cream. I will try it without next time. Huge hit and I am a soup maker... I know soup. :)

