Rating: 3
Delicious! I made this with canola oil rather than butter, Better Than Bouillon vegetable stock instead of chicken broth, and about 1 tsp. of dried herbes de Provence in place of the fresh herbs. I also left out the cream and sugar, and didn't make the croutons (I will next time, but didn't have the ingredients on hand today). The soup came out really flavorful, smooth, and delicious. Highly recommended. Also, a tip for easier squash preparation -- winter squashes are so hard to chop up, so I halve them lengthwise and seed them, and bake them cut-side down on a pan with some oil until a fork can pierce through the skin. Then I take them out, cool, and chop, and add to the soup. Much easier for me than wrestling with them raw.

