I've made this recipe many times, and guests love it! Do yourselves a favor; instead of peeling the squash cut it in half, scoop out the seeds and roast it in the oven @ 375 for about an hour. When it is tender, you can just scoop the pulp out and add it to your pot. This makes the active preparation much shorter! I also like to add a couple of granny smith apples - a little tartness adds to the soup.

