You can add me to the list of those who loved this recipe! I made it exactly as specified, but I think I ended up with more squash than intended, so I used a bit more cream and sugar. Having wrestled with cutting up squash before, I roasted squash halves in a 425-degree oven. I brushed a little butter on each cut side, and found 35 minutes to be plenty. That amount of time added some nice roasty "zest" to the texture, and meant no-muss, no-fuss prep of the squashes. It also cut down on the final simmer time. My guests loved the croutons so much, we ate them all, so there are none left for tomorrow, alas! They also begged to take some home. Try this, you won't be disappointed. And this is coming from someone who usually turns up her nose at squash!

