Rating: 0
Instead of trying to peel the squash, cut it in half or quarters and seed it. Sprinkle it with salt and pepper and roast in the oven at 400 degrees or until it is slightly browned. You can then scoop out the flesh and use it in recipes. Also, if you are pressed for time you can wrap the cooked squash and keep it in the fridge until you need it.

