Rating: 4
This is the best squash soup that I've ever had. We fight over leftovers. To all those who have such trouble peeling the squash: ditch the knife, and use a good vegetable peeler. For acorn squash, slice it between the ribs so that you have melon-like wedges, which are easy to reach with the peeler. You may have to go over it twice, but it's easy and reduces waste. I do agree that it would be nigh impossible to do with a knife.

