Rating: 4
I took the advice from San Francisco and roasted the squash w/garlic cloves and fresh sage in their cavities at 400 degrees for 1.25 hours, and I took Northridge's advice and drizzled a little olive oil on them before roasting. This gave off a wonderful aroma and flavor for the soup. As everyone else says, the gruyere croutons are fantastic. I think the croutons could be used as appetizers as well. The nice thing is that this recipe adapts so well to other substitutions, many of which have already been mentioned by other reviewers here.

