Rating: 4
I usually give 3 forks to my favorite recipes on this site, but this one deserves 4 forks! I roasted the squash, along with the garlic, thereby cutting out the laborious task of peeling and cubing butternut and acorn squash. Eliminating that task made this recipe a more enjoyable one to make...thanks to previous reviewers for that tip. The taste of the thyme with all the other ingredients melded beautifully. I also used half and half instead of cream with great success. Try this one...you will receive lots of compliments with a relatively easy and delicious recipe!

