This is a delicious fall-winter soup. Instead of boiling the squash I cut them in half, sprinkled with olive oil and a little dried sage, placed six un-peeled garlic cloves in the cavities and roasted at 375 until they were tender. Scooped out the roasted squash and garlic and proceeded with the recipe. I think that roasting adds a little depth of flavor, didn't need the sugar as the soup was just perfect without it.

